332
00:42:48,894 --> 00:42:53,916
Letter from Birmingham Jail by Dr. Martin Luther King Jr.

333
00:42:53,936 --> 00:42:56,196
16th April 1963.

334
00:42:59,157 --> 00:43:01,578
My dear fellow clergymen.

335
00:43:02,178 --> 00:43:11,641
While confined here in the Birmingham City Jail, I came across your recent statement calling my present activities unwise and untimely.

336
00:43:12,769 --> 00:43:16,331
Seldom do I pause to answer criticism of my work and ideas.

337
00:43:16,792 --> 00:43:25,797
If I sought to answer all the criticisms that crossed my desk, my secretaries would have little time for anything other than such correspondence in the course of the day.

338
00:43:26,358 --> 00:43:28,839
And I would have no time for constructive work.

339
00:43:29,980 --> 00:43:41,187
Several months ago, the affiliate here in Birmingham asked us to be on call to engage in a nonviolent direct action program if such were deemed necessary.

340
00:43:41,791 --> 00:43:47,096
We readily consented, and when the hour came, we lived up to our promise.

341
00:43:47,757 --> 00:43:55,645
So I, along with several members of my staff, am here because I was invited here.

342
00:43:55,665 --> 00:44:01,270
I am here because I have organizational ties here.

343
00:44:01,811 --> 00:44:06,135
But more basically, I am in Birmingham because injustice is here.

344
00:44:06,982 --> 00:44:31,933
Just as the prophets of the 8th century BC left their villages and carried their thus saith the Lord far beyond the boundaries of their hometowns and just as the apostle Paul left his village in Tarsus and carried the gospel of Jesus Christ to the far corners of the Greco-Roman world, so am I compelled to carry the gospel of freedom beyond my hometown.

345
00:44:32,794 --> 00:44:33,374
Moreover,

346
00:44:34,032 --> 00:44:39,074
I am cognizant of the interrelatedness of all communities and states.

347
00:44:39,954 --> 00:44:46,177
I cannot sit idly by in Atlanta and not be concerned with what happens in Birmingham.

348
00:44:47,117 --> 00:44:51,699
Injustice anywhere is a threat to justice everywhere.

349
00:44:52,519 --> 00:45:00,982
We are caught in an inescapable network of mutuality, tied in a single garment of destiny.

350
00:45:01,762 --> 00:45:03,623
Whatever affects one directly

351
00:45:04,161 --> 00:45:06,622
affects all indirectly.

352
00:45:07,402 --> 00:45:14,625
Never again can we afford to live with the narrow, provincial, outside agitator idea.

353
00:45:15,926 --> 00:45:19,467
In any nonviolent campaign, there are four basic steps.

354
00:45:20,227 --> 00:45:23,889
Collection of the facts to determine whether injustices exist.

355
00:45:24,669 --> 00:45:29,211
Negotiation, self-purification, and direct action.

356
00:45:30,091 --> 00:45:32,552
We have gone through all the steps in Birmingham.

357
00:45:33,396 --> 00:45:39,238
There can be no gain saying that the fact racial injustice engulfs this community.

358
00:45:39,979 --> 00:45:42,800
Its ugly record of brutality is widely known.

359
00:45:43,480 --> 00:45:50,903
There have been unsolved bombings of Negro homes and churches in Birmingham more than in any other city in the nation.

360
00:45:51,603 --> 00:45:54,444
These are the hard, brutal facts of the case.

361
00:45:54,984 --> 00:45:56,765
So we must see the need

362
00:45:57,187 --> 00:46:11,214
for non-violent gadflies to create the kind of tension in society that will help men rise from the dark depths of prejudice and racism to the majestic heights of understanding and brotherhood.

363
00:46:12,014 --> 00:46:24,040
The purpose of our direct action program is to create a situation so crisis-packed that it will inevitably open the door to negotiation.

364
00:46:24,679 --> 00:46:33,747
Too long has our beloved Southland been bogged down in a tragic effort to live in monologue rather than dialogue.

365
00:46:34,348 --> 00:46:40,974
We have waited for more than 340 years for our constitutional and God-given rights.

366
00:46:41,975 --> 00:46:46,780
Perhaps it is easy for those who have never felt the stinging dots of segregation to say, wait.

367
00:46:48,965 --> 00:47:18,643
But when you have seen vicious mobs lynch your mothers and fathers at will and drown your sisters and brothers at whim, when you have seen hate-filled policemen curse, kick, and even kill your black brothers and sisters, when you suddenly find your tongue twisted and your speech stammering as you seek to explain to your six-year-old daughter why she can't go to the public amusement park and see tears welling up in her eyes when she is told that

368
00:47:19,037 --> 00:47:22,160
Funtown is closed to colored children.

369
00:47:22,920 --> 00:47:43,539
I had hoped that the white moderate would understand that the present tension in the South is a necessary phase of the transition from an obnoxious negative peace, in which the Negro passively accepted his unjust plight, to a substantive and positive peace in which all men will respect the dignity and worth of human personality.

370
00:47:44,340 --> 00:47:44,740
Actually,

371
00:47:45,230 --> 00:47:50,732
We who engage in non-violent direct action are not the creators of tension.

372
00:47:51,873 --> 00:47:57,755
We merely bring it to the surface, bring to surface the hidden tension that is already alive.

373
00:47:58,295 --> 00:48:02,997
We bring it out in the open where it can be seen and dealt with.

374
00:48:03,777 --> 00:48:08,139
I stand in the middle of two opposing forces in the Negro community.

375
00:48:09,319 --> 00:48:10,920
One is a force of complacency.

376
00:48:11,723 --> 00:48:39,056
made up in part of Negroes who, as a result of long years of oppression, are so drained of self-respect and a sense of somebody-ness that they have adjusted to a degree, and in part of a few middle-class Negroes who, because of a degree of academic and economic security, and because in some ways they profit by segregation, have become insensitive to the problems of the masses.

377
00:48:39,980 --> 00:48:48,062
The other force is one of bitterness and hatred, and it comes perilously close to advocating violence.

378
00:48:48,802 --> 00:48:56,863
Oppressed people cannot remain oppressed forever, so I have not said to my people, get rid of your discontent.

379
00:48:57,324 --> 00:49:08,946
Rather, I have tried to say that this normal and healthy discontent can be channeled into the creative outlet of nonviolent direct action.

380
00:49:10,435 --> 00:49:13,016
and pray long prayers.

381
00:49:14,437 --> 00:49:24,121
If I have said anything in this letter that overstates the truth and indicates an unreasonable patience, I beg you to forgive me.

382
00:49:25,162 --> 00:49:37,847
If I have said anything that understates the truth and indicates my having a patience that allows me to settle for anything less than brotherhood, I beg God to forgive me.

383
00:49:39,125 --> 00:49:41,746
I hope this letter finds you strong in the faith.

384
00:49:42,626 --> 00:49:58,692
Let us all hope that the dark clouds of racial prejudice will soon pass away and in some not-too-distant tomorrow the radiant stars of love and brotherhood will shine over our great nation with all their scintillating beauty.

385
00:49:59,792 --> 00:50:05,594
Yours for the cause of peace and brotherhood, Martin Luther King.

